Tushka Public School is excited to release our Return to School Plan for the fall semester. You can view the preliminary plan on our school web-site at
www.tushka.k12.ok.us As we have seen, this is a very fluid situation so if any changes or additions are made to the plan we will post them on the school web-site and our school FaceBook page. Thank you for your patience during this time. We look forward to seeing our students on August 6th!!!!

Atoka County Medical Center
June 12 at 1:47 PM ·

Atoka County Medical Center is excited to sponsor the Atoka County Schools 2020 Junior & Senior Prom. The event will be open to all Junior & Seniors within Atoka County District.

The 2020 Junior & Senior Prom will be located at the Atoka Community Center on Friday, July 17, 2020 from 7 p.m. - 10 p.m.

Any business or individual that would like to donate to the event please contact 580.364.8151.

post_text:
Our first day of Grab & Go Meals was a great success! Thank you to Tushka's Child Nutrition Staff for working to feed our kids!
However, we are going to make one change moving forward... In order help people not have to make two trips a day, we will be serving breakfast and lunch at the same pick-up. You will now be able to get both meals, to go, from 9:00AM to 11:00AM. We hope this change helps make the process more convenient for parents and students!
Please Share!

post_text:
In an effort to ease the burden of a two week school shutdown, Tushka School will be providing Grab & Go Meals to our students. We will be providing both breakfast and lunch. All meals can be picked up at the front of the main building, directly inside the Elementary School entrance. Breakfast can be picked up between 8:30AM - 9:30AM, and lunch between 11:00AM - 12:00PM. These meals will be served on days Tushka School would have been in session. Please see school calendar.

Please Share!

post_text:
Tushka Schools Stakeholders,
The State Board of Education voted to suspend school operations for public schools in Oklahoma. With this decision, Tushka Public Schools will suspend ALL school activities and close ALL school facilities until April 6th, 2020. We will continue to update as new information is available. I apologize for this inconvenience, however the safety and well being of our students is the top priority.
Please Share!

post_text:
We were just informed by the Tushka Water Department that there has been a break in a main water line that will leave Tushka without water. They are projecting that this last until at least 5:00PM today. We were able to serve our students lunch, however will need to make arrangements to have students picked up or confirmation that someone will be at home for bus riders. We are going to run our bus routes at 1:00pm. We will not send our young students home without knowing they are attended. I apologize for this inconvenience.
If you can contact your child's office and make arrangements for pick-up or bus drop off, please do so now. PLEASE SHARE!

post_text: Due to many recent unforeseen circumstances, we recognize the need for a quick and effective way to get messages out to our parents, students, and community. To help with this, we have set up an Official Tushka School Facebook page for updates, announcements, and notifications. Keep in mind there will still be many additional resources available for parents, students, and teachers though our school website (www.tushka.k12.ok.us.) Please share and watch for updates, schedules, schedule changes, school closings, etc....
